tic distance\nambiguities is a quick and reliable method in most cases, with an 80% success\nrate in determining the correct designation of whether an object is at the near\nor far distance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Nov 2005 14:37:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
