 GRBs and show that they lie at the very faint\nend of the distribution. These two bursts are good examples of a population of\nbursts with dark or faint afterglows that are being unveiled through the\nincreasing usage of large diameter telescopes engaged in comprehensive\nobservational programmes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Nov 2005 14:20:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
